HEADWORD: Mannerist
<hw>Man"ner*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mani⟦eacute⟧riste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One addicted to mannerism; a
person who, in action, bearing, or treatment, carries characteristic
peculiarities to excess. See citation under
<er>Mannerism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

